=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_DC_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 459 Hz, featuring punchy attack and compressed envelope, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 459.4793
  harmonic_decay_rate: -11.6113
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5005
  pitch_clarity: 0.0808
  inharmonicity: 0.0103
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.6229
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: DC Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/DC.html
// Tags: DC, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// won't work (the output is 0.5*0.0), which is why we need the DC UGen!
{ 0.5 }.play

// constantly zero
{ DC.ar(0.0) }.play;


// DC offset; will click on start and finish
{ DC.ar(0.5) + SinOsc.ar(440, 0, 0.1) }.play;


// test - note the transient before LeakDC adapts and suppresses the offset
{ LeakDC.ar(DC.ar(0.5)) }.play;


// show scope
s.play
